<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,866,972]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">This group is distinguished by having the prefrontal shield fused with the rostral shield, a small anterior supralabial and a subtriangular cloacal shield. Most species have a tall posterior supralabial which reaches the level of the eye and are uniform black above and below. The robust skull usually has fused parietals.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
